# Error Handling and User Feedback

## Error Handling Strategy

### Error Types
Handle different types of errors appropriately:

1. **Network Errors**: Connection timeouts, no internet
2. **API Errors**: Server errors, validation errors, authentication errors
3. **Validation Errors**: Form validation, input validation
4. **Business Logic Errors**: Application-specific errors
5. **System Errors**: Unexpected errors, crashes

### Error Hierarchy
```dart
// Base error class
abstract class AppError {
  final String message;
  final String? code;
  
  AppError(this.message, {this.code});
}

// Specific error types
class NetworkError extends AppError {
  NetworkError(super.message, {super.code});
}

class ApiError extends AppError {
  final int? statusCode;
  ApiError(super.message, {super.code, this.statusCode});
}

class ValidationError extends AppError {
  ValidationError(super.message, {super.code});
}

class BusinessLogicError extends AppError {
  BusinessLogicError(super.message, {super.code});
}
```

## User Feedback Patterns

### AppSnackBar Usage
Use [AppSnackBar](mdc:lib/core/utils/app_snack_bar.dart) for consistent user feedback:

```dart
// Success messages
AppSnackBar.success(message: 'Operation completed successfully');

// Error messages
AppSnackBar.error(message: 'Something went wrong');

// Warning messages
AppSnackBar.warning(message: 'Please check your input');

// Info messages
AppSnackBar.info(message: 'Information message');

// Custom snackbar with action
AppSnackBar.show(
  message: 'File deleted',
  type: SnackBarType.success,
  onPress: () => _undoDelete(),
  buttonText: 'Undo',
);
```

### SnackBar Types
The app supports four snackbar types:

```dart
enum SnackBarType { success, info, warning, error }

// Success: Green border, checkmark icon
// Info: Blue border, info icon  
// Warning: Orange border, warning icon
// Error: Red border, error icon
```

## API Error Handling

### Result Pattern
Use the `Result` pattern for API responses:

```dart
Future<Result<BaseResponse<UserModel>, String>> getUser() async {
  try {
    final response = await _apiService.getUser();
    return Success(response);
  } catch (e) {
    return Failure(_handleError(e));
  }
}
```

### Error Handling in Controllers
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  Future<void> loadData() async {
    try {
      isLoading(true);
      hasError(false);
      
      final result = await _repository.fetchData();
      
      result.when(
        (response) {
          // Handle success
          if (response.data != null) {
            dataList.value = response.data!;
          }
        },
        (error) {
          // Handle error
          hasError(true);
          errorMessage.value = error;
          AppSnackBar.error(message: error);
        },
      );
    } catch (e) {
      // Handle unexpected errors
      hasError(true);
      errorMessage.value = 'An unexpected error occurred';
      AppSnackBar.error(message: 'An unexpected error occurred');
    } finally {
      isLoading(false);
    }
  }
}
```

### Network Error Handling
```dart
class NetworkErrorHandler {
  static String handleDioException(DioException e) {
    switch (e.type) {
      case DioExceptionType.connectionTimeout:
        return 'Connection timeout. Please check your internet connection.';
      case DioExceptionType.sendTimeout:
        return 'Request timeout. Please try again.';
      case DioExceptionType.receiveTimeout:
        return 'Response timeout. Please try again.';
      case DioExceptionType.badResponse:
        return _handleHttpError(e.response?.statusCode);
      case DioExceptionType.cancel:
        return 'Request was cancelled.';
      case DioExceptionType.connectionError:
        return 'No internet connection. Please check your network.';
      default:
        return 'Network error occurred. Please try again.';
    }
  }
  
  static String _handleHttpError(int? statusCode) {
    switch (statusCode) {
      case 400:
        return 'Bad request. Please check your input.';
      case 401:
        return 'Unauthorized. Please sign in again.';
      case 403:
        return 'Access denied. You don\'t have permission.';
      case 404:
        return 'Resource not found.';
      case 422:
        return 'Validation error. Please check your input.';
      case 500:
        return 'Server error. Please try again later.';
      default:
        return 'An error occurred. Please try again.';
    }
  }
}
```

## Form Error Handling

### Validation Errors
Handle form validation errors gracefully:

```dart
class SignInController extends BaseViewController with ValidationMixin {
  RxString formError = ''.obs;
  
  Future<void> onSignIn() async {
    // Clear previous errors
    formError.value = '';
    
    if (formKey.currentState?.validate() ?? false) {
      final result = await _repository.signIn(formData);
      
      result.when(
        (response) {
          // Handle success
          Get.offAllNamed(RoutesName.homeView);
        },
        (error) {
          // Handle API errors
          if (error.contains('validation')) {
            formError.value = error;
          } else {
            AppSnackBar.error(message: error);
          }
        },
      );
    }
  }
}
```

### Real-time Error Display
```dart
class FeatureView extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return GetBuilder<FeatureController>(
      builder: (controller) => Scaffold(
        body: Column(
          children: [
            // Form fields
            TextFormField(
              controller: controller.emailController,
              validator: controller.emailValidator,
              decoration: InputDecoration(
                labelText: 'Email',
                errorText: controller.emailError.value.isNotEmpty 
                  ? controller.emailError.value 
                  : null,
              ),
            ),
            
            // Global form error
            Obx(() {
              if (controller.formError.value.isNotEmpty) {
                return Container(
                  padding: EdgeInsets.all(12),
                  margin: EdgeInsets.symmetric(vertical: 8),
                  decoration: BoxDecoration(
                    color: Colors.red.shade50,
                    border: Border.all(color: Colors.red.shade200),
                    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(8),
                  ),
                  child: Text(
                    controller.formError.value,
                    style: TextStyle(color: Colors.red.shade700),
                  ),
                );
              }
              return SizedBox.shrink();
            }),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Loading States

### Loading State Management
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  RxBool isLoading = false.obs;
  RxBool isSubmitting = false.obs;
  RxBool isRefreshing = false.obs;
  
  Future<void> loadData() async {
    isLoading(true);
    try {
      // Load data
    } finally {
      isLoading(false);
    }
  }
  
  Future<void> submitForm() async {
    isSubmitting(true);
    try {
      // Submit form
    } finally {
      isSubmitting(false);
    }
  }
}
```

### Loading UI Patterns
```dart
// Loading overlay
Obx(() {
  if (controller.isLoading.value) {
    return Stack(
      children: [
        // Main content
        _buildContent(),
        
        // Loading overlay
        Container(
          color: Colors.black.withOpacity(0.3),
          child: Center(
            child: CircularProgressIndicator(),
          ),
        ),
      ],
    );
  }
  return _buildContent();
});

// Loading button
Obx(() => ElevatedButton(
  onPressed: controller.isSubmitting.value ? null : controller.onSubmit,
  child: controller.isSubmitting.value
    ? SizedBox(
        width: 20,
        height: 20,
        child: CircularProgressIndicator(strokeWidth: 2),
      )
    : Text('Submit'),
));
```

## Error Recovery

### Retry Mechanisms
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  int retryCount = 0;
  static const int maxRetries = 3;
  
  Future<void> loadDataWithRetry() async {
    try {
      await loadData();
      retryCount = 0; // Reset on success
    } catch (e) {
      if (retryCount < maxRetries) {
        retryCount++;
        await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 2));
        loadDataWithRetry();
      } else {
        AppSnackBar.error(message: 'Failed after $maxRetries attempts');
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Fallback UI
```dart
class FeatureView extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return GetBuilder<FeatureController>(
      builder: (controller) => Scaffold(
        body: Obx(() {
          if (controller.isLoading.value) {
            return Center(child: CircularProgressIndicator());
          }
          
          if (controller.hasError.value) {
            return _buildErrorWidget(controller);
          }
          
          return _buildContent(controller);
        }),
      ),
    );
  }
  
  Widget _buildErrorWidget(FeatureController controller) {
    return Center(
      child: Column(
        mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
        children: [
          Icon(Icons.error_outline, size: 64, color: Colors.red),
          SizedBox(height: 16),
          Text(
            'Something went wrong',
            style: TextStyle(fontSize: 18, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
          ),
          SizedBox(height: 8),
          Text(
            controller.errorMessage.value,
            textAlign: TextAlign.center,
            style: TextStyle(color: Colors.grey[600]),
          ),
          SizedBox(height: 24),
          ElevatedButton(
            onPressed: controller.retry,
            child: Text('Try Again'),
          ),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Logging and Debugging

### Error Logging
```dart
class ErrorLogger {
  static void logError(String message, {Object? error, StackTrace? stackTrace}) {
    if (kDebugMode) {
      print('ERROR: $message');
      if (error != null) print('Error: $error');
      if (stackTrace != null) print('Stack: $stackTrace');
    }
    
    // In production, send to crash reporting service
    // FirebaseCrashlytics.instance.recordError(error, stackTrace);
  }
  
  static void logApiError(String endpoint, int? statusCode, String message) {
    logError('API Error: $endpoint', error: 'Status: $statusCode, Message: $message');
  }
}
```

### Debug Information
```dart
class DebugInfo {
  static void showErrorDetails(String message, {Object? error}) {
    if (kDebugMode) {
      Get.dialog(
        AlertDialog(
          title: Text('Error Details'),
          content: Column(
            mainAxisSize: MainAxisSize.min,
            crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
            children: [
              Text('Message: $message'),
              if (error != null) ...[
                SizedBox(height: 8),
                Text('Error: $error'),
              ],
            ],
          ),
          actions: [
            TextButton(
              onPressed: () => Get.back(),
              child: Text('Close'),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      );
    }
  }
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Error Handling
- Always handle errors gracefully
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors for debugging
- Implement retry mechanisms where appropriate

### 2. User Experience
- Show loading states during operations
- Provide clear feedback for all actions
- Use appropriate UI patterns for different error types
- Allow users to recover from errors

### 3. Error Messages
- Use user-friendly language
- Be specific about what went wrong
- Provide actionable guidance
- Avoid technical jargon

### 4. Performance
- Don't block the UI during error handling
- Use appropriate loading indicators
- Handle errors asynchronously
- Implement proper cleanup

### 5. Testing
- Test error scenarios
- Verify error messages
- Test retry mechanisms
- Validate error recovery flows

### 6. Monitoring
- Log errors for analysis
- Track error rates
- Monitor user experience
- Implement crash reporting